\begin{abstract}
The discovery of apparent cosmological acceleration has spawned a huge number of dark energy and modified gravity theories. The $f\left(\mathcal{R}\right)$ models of gravity are obtained when one replaces the Ricci scalar in the Einstein-Hilbert action by an arbitrary function $f\left(\mathcal{R}\right)$,

